Value.value: The Bloodmoon Orcs were once slaves to the petty tyrants of Stonehold. Those rulers used the Bloodmoon Orcs as an enslaved army, and they were notorious for making night raids on surrounding villages and sparing very few people from death. Thus the crude rendition of their brand on this post, a bleeding crescent moon, makes a great deal of sense.

The crescent moon in this crude rendition of the Bloodmoon Orc brand bows to the left. There appear to be six great blotches of blood in the middle of the crescent, a large scar of blood surrounded by five smaller splatterings. Each tip of the crescent is as sharp as the point of an elven blade... by the Seldarine, could this be a bastardization of the symbol of Corellon Larethian?

A crude rendition of the Bloodmoon Orc brand decorates this post. Moons are awesome, and so is blood, and a bloody moon is the best of both worlds. It is very intimidating, especially since the blood on this one, though dried, was someone's real blood!
